en_121317_0	Sri Lanka Light Infantry (SLLI) troops in a colourful and magnificent ceremony, held at the SLLI Regimental Headquarters premises in Panagoda on Friday (5) bade farewell to their outgoing Colonel of the Regiment, Major General J. Ruwan Kulatunga who retired from the Army after a distinguished career spanning over three decades.
en_121317_1	In keeping with military traditions, he was greeted to a Guard Turnout at the entrance and a subsequent Guard of Honour parade by regimental troops after he was taken to the parade ground by Colonel D.A.K Dissanayake, Centre Commandant SLLI and the parade commander.
en_121317_2	After a while, Major General Kulathunaga laid floral wreaths at the colossal SLLI War Heroes' monument.
en_121317_3	As the stage was set, he recalled his moving memories and addressed the SLLI troops who were there to see him off.
en_121317_4	Several group photographs with him added memories to the event.
en_121317_5	An all rank tea arrangement at the Warrant Officers’ and Sergeants’ Mess in the premises enabled him to share a couple of thoughts with them.
en_121317_6	The programme of events culminated with a ‘Guest Night’ hosted for Major General Kulatunga and Mrs Thushari Kulatunga by Officers and their spouses in the Regimental Officers’ Mess as the dusk fell.
en_121317_7	On behalf of all members of the Sri Lanka Light Infantry, the incoming Colonel of the Regiment Major General L. Mahinda Mudalige presented a memento to the day's protagonist wishing him best of luck in his future endeavours.
en_121317_8	Major General J. Ruwan Kulatunga born in Wellawatta received his education from Nalanda College in Colombo as a very clever student in both academic and sport spheres.
en_121317_9	He was a very popular sportsman in the school cricket and hockey teams.
en_121317_10	During his school period, he was the cadet sergeant in the school Cadet Platoon.
en_121317_11	Enlisted to the Sri Lanka Army as an Officer Cadet on 05 of March 1984, he thereafter completed his initial Officer Cadet training at the prestigious Sri Lanka Military Academy in Diyathalawa.
en_121317_12	Upon the culmination of the basic training, he was commissioned as a Second Lieutenant and subsequently posted to the Sri Lanka Light Infantry Regiment of the Sri Lanka Army on 16 of November 1985.
en_121317_13	He has followed numerous local and overseas courses in various fields of studies enhancing his professional knowledge in an impressive manner.
en_121317_14	In addition to the courses he followed in India, different professional ones he followed in Malaysia, Romania, Pakistan, United States of America and the Philippines were very significant and provided him with an ocean of professional knowledge in the international sphere as well.
en_121317_15	He has received a Masters Degree in the field of National Security Administration from the University of the Philippines.
en_121317_16	In his extended military career over the period of 35 years, he rendered his voluble service in various capacities in Command, Instructional and Staff appointments from the elementary level up to the higher level to-date.
en_121317_17	Among several key appointments, he held were Commanding Officer of Sri Lanka Military Academy, Commandant of Sri Lanka Military Academy, Colonel of the Regiment Mechanized Infantry, Deputy Vice Chancellor of Kotelawala Defence University, Commandant of the Defence Services Command and Staff College and Colonel of the Regiment of Sri Lanka Light Infantry Regiment.
en_121317_18	During his tour of duty, he has commanded 8th Battalion of Sri Lanka Light Infantry as a Commanding Officer and 534 Brigade, 516 Brigade, 552 Brigade, 512 Brigade as a Brigade Commander.
en_121317_19	Further, he commanded the 55 Infantry Division and the 12 Infantry Division as a General Officer Commanding and also as the Commander of the Security Forces- Wanni.
en_121317_20	During his brave military career, he has contributed to almost all the operations which have been conducted against the LTTE from the year 1984 up until the decisive victory of the last humanitarian operation in May 2009.
en_121317_21	His exceptional unique performances during operations against the LTTE have been well-recognized as a battlefield commander and was decorated with Rana Soora Padakkama (RSP) for his gallantry acts during the operations.
en_121317_22	He is currently serving as the Chief of National Intelligence in the Ministry of Defence.
